rs be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_operator','draft','2026-03-21 02:37:38',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('bf3d0cbc-2e44-4ad1-8912-46e7f34b18cb','41281936-00ec-4398-9bbe-dde5783b1451','GPU financing — a quick thought','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi J.J.,</p>\n\n  <p>I''ll keep this short. Vultr is building serious GPU infrastructure — Independent cloud provider valued at $3.5bn, actively expanding GPU capacity for AI workloads.. The financing piece is where we can help.</p>\n\n  <p>We help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.</p>\n\n  <p>The short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi J.J.,\n\nI''ll keep this short. Vultr is building serious GPU infrastructure — Independent cloud provider valued at $3.5bn, actively expanding GPU capacity for AI workloads.. The financing piece is where we can help.\n\nWe help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.\n\nThe short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_operator','draft','2026-03-21 02:37:38',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('cf53a004-ac98-4645-8dcf-998dc22483d0','2b168fae-478d-4a86-b85c-5737cd77f1f8','GPU financing — a quick thought','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi Joakim,</p>\n\n  <p>I''ll keep this short. Verda is building serious GPU infrastructure — European AI cloud operator (formerly DataCrunch). Raised $64M Series A including debt component. Focused on EU AI compute.. The financing piece is where we can help.</p>\n\n  <p>We help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.</p>\n\n  <p>The short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi Joakim,\n\nI''ll keep this short. Verda is building serious GPU infrastructure — European AI cloud operator (formerly DataCrunch). Raised $64M Series A including debt component. Focused on EU AI compute.. The financing piece is where we can help.\n\nWe help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.\n\nThe short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_operator','draft','2026-03-21 02:37:38',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('1d1a3555-124e-4848-acee-dc5ee879393f','ccdc4b92-26fb-448d-8ccd-5dfde7149789','GPU-backed credit — the residual value question','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi David,</p>\n\n  <p>Upper90 is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed private credit fund. Led the Crusoe Energy credit facility — a landmark GPU infrastructure financing deal.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?</p>\n\n  <p>We help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.</p>\n\n  <p>It''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi David,\n\nUpper90 is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed private credit fund. Led the Crusoe Energy credit facility — a landmark GPU infrastructure financing deal.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?\n\nWe help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.\n\nIt''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_lender','draft','2026-03-21 02:40:08',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('504c6699-f5a2-48c4-a311-72df9dd26ad7','837ee315-f839-43e7-be5f-2ad693525c17','GPU-backed credit — the residual value question','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi Richard,</p>\n\n  <p>Victory Park Capital is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed credit specialist with expertise in technology and infrastructure lending. Active in alternative asset finance.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?</p>\n\n  <p>We help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.</p>\n\n  <p>It''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi Richard,\n\nVictory Park Capital is active in AI infrastructure credit — Asset-backed credit specialist with expertise in technology and infrastructure lending. Active in alternative asset finance.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?\n\nWe help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.\n\nIt''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_lender','draft','2026-03-21 02:40:08',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('32b5d5fd-baee-45e1-8c48-7a5d3c0a2f15','c647e36e-a684-47d7-ab73-762ecd8ce6d8','GPU-backed credit — the residual value question','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi Research,</p>\n\n  <p>Armada Credit Partners is active in AI infrastructure credit — Credit fund that financed the Verda (DataCrunch) expansion. Specialist in technology and infrastructure debt.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?</p>\n\n  <p>We help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.</p>\n\n  <p>It''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi Research,\n\nArmada Credit Partners is active in AI infrastructure credit — Credit fund that financed the Verda (DataCrunch) expansion. Specialist in technology and infrastructure debt.. The question we keep hearing from lenders is: what are the GPUs worth at maturity?\n\nWe help lenders make more GPU-backed loans by protecting downside on future collateral value. The deal economics look great until someone asks about end-of-term hardware value. We give you a cleaner answer.\n\nIt''s meant to make the deal easier to underwrite — a cleaner IC story, better recovery assumptions, more confidence to deploy. Not add complexity.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? We can show you how it fits the credit box.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_lender','draft','2026-03-21 02:40:08',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('2b544455-8379-4975-9d8b-c0103dd309e0','05ee1994-a747-42f1-86e3-3d00bab53283','GPU financing — a quick thought','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi Marcus,</p>\n\n  <p>I''ll keep this short. Voltage Park is building serious GPU infrastructure — Test manual note. The financing piece is where we can help.</p>\n\n  <p>We help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.</p>\n\n  <p>The short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi Marcus,\n\nI''ll keep this short. Voltage Park is building serious GPU infrastructure — Test manual note. The financing piece is where we can help.\n\nWe help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.\n\nThe short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_operator','draft','2026-03-21 02:51:42',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('d6ab4613-21d5-4820-aa1e-d6ba755810c1','05ee1994-a747-42f1-86e3-3d00bab53283','GPU financing — a quick thought','{"html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, ''Segoe UI'', sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.6; color: #1a1a1a; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 0 0 16px; }\n    a { color: #2563eb; }\n    .signature { margin-top: 28px; color: #555; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>Hi Marcus,</p>\n\n  <p>I''ll keep this short. Voltage Park is building serious GPU infrastructure — Test manual note. The financing piece is where we can help.</p>\n\n  <p>We help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.</p>\n\n  <p>The short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.</p>\n\n  <p>Would a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"signature\">\n    <p>Josh Augustine<br>\n    Corgi<br>\n    <a href=\"https://corgi.xyz\">corgi.xyz</a></p>\n  </div>\n\n  \n</body>\n</html>","text":"Hi Marcus,\n\nI''ll keep this short. Voltage Park is building serious GPU infrastructure — Test manual note. The financing piece is where we can help.\n\nWe help GPU operators get a better debt structure by reducing residual value risk on the hardware. A lot of lenders still get stuck on one question: what are the GPUs worth at maturity? We solve for that.\n\nThe short version: lenders get more comfort on future hardware value, which can mean better LTV, longer tenor, or lower spread on your next cluster.\n\nWould a 20-minute call with our founders be useful? Happy to work around your schedule.\n\nJosh Augustine\nCorgi\ncorgi.xyz"}','cold_intro_operator','draft','2026-03-21 02:51:42',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('a1377e49-caf1-4937-af76-de7a5dc63189','45a8348a-0bc7-4288-861e-79e4dffa7c7c','Reducing residual value risk on your GPU fleet',unistr('Hi President,\u000a\u000aI''ll keep this short.\u000a\u000aCorgi provides a residual value floor on data-center GPUs — the part of the underwriting that makes lenders nervous about hardware value at maturity (typically 3–5 years out).\u000a\u000aFor a GPU operator like ALTA Technologies, this translates directly into a better debt structure: lower spread, longer tenor, or higher leverage — because lenders have a clear floor on collateral value.\u000a\u000aWe work with GPU owners and their lenders to make financing cleaner. Not adding complexity — removing the one piece that typically slows deals down.\u000a\u000aWorth a 20-minute call with our founders, Isaac and Josh, to see if this fits your current or upcoming financing plans?\u000a\u000aBest,\u000aCorgi Team'),'Cold Intro — GPU Operator','draft','2026-03-23 00:25:00',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'info@altatechnologies.com');
INSERT INTO email_drafts VALUES('f312a86f-00a7-4ab0-afe0-25f14df85b1e','0756a253-f424-46c7-8b70-5b61f0b31aaa','GPU residual value — new specialty line opportunity',unistr('Hi Lauren,\u000a\u000aI wanted to flag an emerging capacity opportunity we think is well-suited for AXIS Capital.\u000a\u000aThe GPU infrastructure market is crossing $100B in financed assets — and the core underwriting challenge is residual value at maturity. Lenders want to deploy into AI infra but need a clear floor on hardware value 3–5 years out. That''s where Corgi comes in.\u000a\u000aThe structure is analogous to automotive residual value programs — an asset class with a proven reinsurance track record — applied to data-center GPUs. The market is early, deal flow is growing, and there''s real capacity need from well-capitalised counterparties.\u000a\u000aOur founders, Isaac and Josh, are building out the reinsurance relationships now. Would it make sense to have a brief introductory call?\u000a\u000aBest,\u000aCorgi Team'),'Cold Intro — Reinsurer/Arranger','draft','2026-03-23 00:25:00',NULL,'a',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'lkent@axiscapital.com');
